# BCOS .gitignore template
#
# Generated by .claude/scripts/set_profile.sh based on the active profile in
# .claude/bcos-profile. DO NOT edit .gitignore by hand — edit this template
# (or the profile) and re-run the script.
#
# Profile markers:
#   # === ALWAYS ===        ignored in every profile
#   # === SHARED ONLY ===   only ignored when profile = "shared"
#   # === PERSONAL ONLY === only ignored when profile = "personal"
#
# When the script runs, it strips the blocks that don't apply to the chosen
# profile and writes the result to .gitignore.

# === ALWAYS ===
# (these are ignored regardless of profile — secrets, OS noise, machine-local)

# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Environment / secrets — NEVER commit, even in private repos
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# IDE files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.project
.settings/
.classpath

# Python cache
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Temporary files
*.tmp
*.temp

# Local Claude Code settings (machine-specific paths)
.claude/settings.local.json

# Hook state (session-specific, machine-local)
.claude/hook_state/*
!.claude/hook_state/.gitkeep

# Agent worktrees (per-session ephemeral copies; large, machine-local)
.claude/worktrees/

# Self-learning ladder event log + derived state (kept ignored even on
# personal — append-only JSONL across multi-machine workflows produces
# guaranteed merge conflicts; the auditor's reversal-rate thresholds depend
# on a complete history that git checkout --theirs would silently truncate.
# Sync via Syncthing if cross-machine continuity matters; never via git.)
.claude/quality/ecosystem/resolutions.jsonl
.claude/quality/ecosystem/learned-rules.json
.claude/quality/ecosystem/learning-blocklist.json
.claude/quality/ecosystem/state.json

# Syncthing marker folder (per-machine sync setup, not repo content)
.stfolder/

# Syncthing ignore config (per-machine, not repo content; reveals maintainer sync setup)
.stignore

# Dashboard runtime state (per-machine; the code ships, the runtime doesn't)
.claude/scripts/bcos-dashboard/__pycache__/

# === SHARED ONLY ===
# (BCOS dropped into a multi-tenant or team repo — keep host codebase clean
# of runtime artifacts AND maintainer-only files. On personal profile, the
# items in this block become tracked so they sync across the maintainer's
# workstations via the private repo. publish.sh's DEV_ONLY_PATHS strips
# them at squash time when publishing to a downstream public repo.)

# Quality session data (keep directory structure)
.claude/quality/sessions/*
!.claude/quality/sessions/.gitkeep

# Lessons (user-specific, accumulates over time — starter template ships instead)
.claude/quality/ecosystem/lessons.json

# Auto-generated wake-up context (regenerated per user)
docs/.wake-up-context.md

# Session diary (per-user accumulated session notes — append-only;
# multi-machine sync via Syncthing if needed, never via git)
docs/.session-diary.md

# Auto-generated document index (regenerated per user)
docs/document-index.md

# Daily digest (runtime output, overwritten each morning)
docs/_inbox/daily-digest.md
docs/_inbox/daily-digest.json

# Umbrella node registration — per-install file pointing at the umbrella host.
# In SHARED profile (public / multi-tenant repos) this leaks the umbrella id
# and local sibling layout, so we gitignore. In PERSONAL profile this is
# treated as portable per-portfolio config and committed (so siblings re-cloned
# on a new workstation come with the umbrella binding already attached).
.bcos-umbrella.json

# Active plan workspaces — implementation plans, manifests, pre-flight notes,
# and review captures live here while a feature is being built. The folder
# itself is tracked (.gitkeep below) so installs scaffold it; the per-plan
# subfolders stay local until the plan is folded back into framework docs.
docs/_planned/*/
!docs/_planned/.gitkeep

# Maintainer-private docs — strategy notes, client context, draft architecture.
# Personal profile tracks them (sync across maintainer workstations); shared
# profile ignores them (host repo doesn't see them). publish.sh strips on
# any push to a public downstream.
.private/

# Repo-specific maintainer scripts and dev infrastructure — tracked on
# personal so the maintainer's workstations stay in sync; ignored on shared.
.claude/scripts/publish.sh
.claude/scripts/bcos-galaxy/
.claude/scripts/test_*.py
.claude/scripts/fixtures/
.claude/hooks/pre_commit_validate.sh

# Schedule dispatcher live config — cadence is a project decision, so the
# maintainer wants it consistent across their workstations. The template
# always ships (schedule-config.template.json); this is the live derivative.
# Per-machine cron times live on the OS-level scheduled task itself, not
# here.
.claude/quality/schedule-config.json

# Update script reference file — snapshot of upstream framework state for
# this install. On personal: the maintainer's snapshot, syncs with their
# other workstations. On shared: per-install, intentionally not shared.
.claude/bcos-claude-reference.md

# Top-level tests/ — fixtures + integration helpers used by gitignored
# .claude/scripts/test_*.py. Without the test scripts (which never ship),
# fixtures are dead weight on the public repo. Convention: all test
# scaffolding stays local; rebuild fixtures from the framework's own
# documented schemas if you need them.
tests/

# Derived artifacts — regenerated from disk on every install via
# refresh_ecosystem_state.py / build_document_index.py / bcos_inventory.py.
# Shipping the dev's snapshot of these would push the framework repo's
# own state to every install, which is misleading and noisy. Each one
# carries a regenerator script that runs as part of update.py / install.sh.
.claude/quality/bcos-inventory.json
.claude/quality/context-index.json
docs/bcos-control-map.md

# === PERSONAL ONLY ===
# (BCOS as a personal knowledge repo, never shared. Knowledge artifacts are
# tracked above — only true machine-local junk goes here. Currently nothing
# extra; reserved for future per-machine artifacts that even personal repos
# shouldn't sync.)
